113 Amani https://www.facebook.com/ahmanieee If you know me, alam mo na super fan ako ng Korean food, and one of our faves is kimbap. Madami nagiisip na mahirap gumawa nito, pero madali lang. The essential ingredients are nori sheet, rice, egg, veggies, and meat of choice. Always consider the quantity and sizes para hindi ka mahirapan magroll. Naisip ko gamitin ang tocino for our kimbap rolls since madalas kaming meron nito plus it can add flavor sa rolls. CHICKEN TOCINO KIMBAP (Makes 3-4 rolls) INGREDIENTS: 1-1 1/2 c uncooked Japanese rice 3-4 dried seaweed (nori) sheets 1 c carrot, julienned 1 c cucumber, julienned (optional) spring onions 1 c cabbage, julienned 3 eggs, beaten 250g King Sue Chicken Tocino (optional) 4 yellow radish pickles (optional) 2-4 fish cake sheets Sesame oil Garlic mayonnaise or plain mayonnaise salt to taste Extra tool: sushi bamboo mat (if not available, you can improvise) PROCEDURE: 1. Cook the rice as usual. 2. Prepare all the vegetables and other ingredients for the filling. 3. Beat 3 eggs with salt to taste; set aside. 4. In a heated pan, lightly cook the fish cake sheet, carrots, cucumber, and cabbage with spring onions (about 1 min per ingredients) separately and over medium heat. 5. Make scrambled eggs; set aside. 6. Cook the King Sue Chicken Tocino as instructed; set aside. 7. Once the rice is cooked, assemble the kimbap. Add sesame oil and salt to the rice. Mix well with a rice spatula. 8. Place one dried seaweed sheet on the bamboo mat (shiny side down). Put the rice on the seaweed sheet, then spread it evenly and thinly to cover about 2/3 of the seaweed. 9. Fill the seaweed with the filling ingredients. Then, roll the seaweed. Set the rolled kimbap aside. 10. Repeat steps 8 & 9 with the remaining ingredients. 11. Slice the kimbap into bite-sized pieces. Serve. 맛있게 드세요!!! 805 Amani https://www.facebook.com/ahmanieee I always find ways to make different dishes for our breakfast lalo na for Andre and his baon para hindi siya maumay. He loves tortilla wrap kaya naisip ko to make something that he will enjoy while also healthy. CHICKEN TOCINO BREAKFAST WRAP INGREDIENTS: 2 tomatoes, sliced 1 c carrot, julienned 1 c cucumber, julienned 1 c cabbage, julienned lettuce 3 eggs, beaten 250g King Sue Chicken Tocino (optional) shredded cheese 3-4 pcs tortilla wrap PROCEDURE: 1. Prepare all the vegetables and other ingredients for the filling. 2. Heat oil in a pan, fry King Sue Chicken Tocino; set aside. 3. Beat 3 eggs with salt to taste and cook the scrambled eggs; set aside. 4. In a heated pan, lightly cook the tomato and onion, carrots, cucumber, and cabbage (about 1 min per ingredient) separately and over medium heat. 5. In the tortilla wrap, assemble the lettuce, tomato, carrots, cucumber and cabbage, scrambled egg, and chicken tocino. Roll into a wrap. 6. Drizzle a small amount of oil in a separate pan, put the breakfast wrap into the pan, and cook for 1-2 mins while turning all sides. Cut in half and serve. You can eat as it is or make a sauce to your liking. Makes 3-4 breakfast wraps.
